{"id":"barren","term":"Barren","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>For a woman to be barren was accounted a severe punishment among the Jews (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 16:2\">Gen. 16:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 30:1\">30:1-23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 1:6\">1 Sam. 1:6</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 1:27\">27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 47:9\">Isa. 47:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 49:21\">49:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 1:25\">Luke 1:25</a>). Instances of barrenness are noticed (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 11:30\">Gen. 11:30</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 25:21\">25:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 29:31\">29:31</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 13:2\">Judg. 13:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 13:3\">3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 1:7\">Luke 1:7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 1:36\">36</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 16:2","Genesis 30:1","1 Samuel 1:6","1 Samuel 1:27","Isaiah 47:9","Isaiah 49:21","Luke 1:25","Genesis 11:30","Genesis 25:21","Genesis 29:31","Judges 13:2","Judges 13:3","Luke 1:7","Luke 1:36"]}